						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab near the temple of Hanumān.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jayasiṁha II—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Jayasiṁhadēva</hi> and mentions <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kundarasa</hi> who had the title ‘lord of Banavāsi.’</p>						

						<p>On grounds of palaeography, the record is assignable to <hi rend="bold">Jayasiṁha II.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
